\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {16}{\ignorespaces A non-LAS baseline: clean-label recovery (MCC) on the per-argument acceptance task, over the same pool and grouped five-fold CV. A feature-based decision tree and the strongest feature learner (random forest / depth-12 tree) plateau well below the LAS route's exact recovery (Sections~\ref {sec:mech}--\ref {sec:exp1}), and closest only on complete/grounded (a single-extension, near-functional target). A per-argument classifier cannot represent the extension \emph  {set} that LAS learns.}}{55}{figure.16}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:baseline_comparison}{{16}{55}{A non-LAS baseline: clean-label recovery (MCC) on the per-argument acceptance task, over the same pool and grouped five-fold CV. A feature-based decision tree and the strongest feature learner (random forest / depth-12 tree) plateau well below the LAS route's exact recovery (Sections~\ref {sec:mech}--\ref {sec:exp1}), and closest only on complete/grounded (a single-extension, near-functional target). A per-argument classifier cannot represent the extension \emph {set} that LAS learns}{figure.16}{}}
